    public abstract class DoublePropertyTransition<E extends javafx.scene.Node>
extends AbstractTransition<E,java.lang.Double>
    A more concrete extension of AbstractTransition. Only the constructor(s), and the get and set methods of a Double property have to be implemented in a subclass. This class makes sure all properties that are of the Double type are animated the same way: if no starting value is set, it is retrieved from the node when the transition starts.
    Author:
    Karim El Assal
